    {
      "id": 156114,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "@shubs and I discovered an instance of Flyte Console on uberinternal.com. After auditing the open source code, we noticed an unauthenticated route for a “CORS proxy”. This was a classic server-side request forgery issue, allowing us to pass an arbitrary request to be performed by the server and read the response. This also allowed reflected cross-site scripting as we could proxy arbitrary HTML documents through it.\n\nWe reported this to both Uber and Flyte, where it was assigned CVE-2022-24856 and quickly resolved.",
